data.text:
-> OSSC CGL Mathematics Test and Mains Exam Date have been released. The exam will be conducted on 30th August and 1st September 2024 respectively (2023 cycle).

-> Candidates can download their e-admit card from 27th August 2024 onwards.

-> The Computer Skill Test for recruitment to the post of CGLRE-2023 will be held on 12.08.2024 in One Sitting at Bhubaneswar and Cuttack. Also, the Prelims Exam Date has been released for 2024 cycle. The exam will be conducted on 6th October 2024.

-> Earlier, the Prelims Exam Dates has been released for recruitment to the post of Combined Graduate Level Recruitment Examination for Group-B & Group-C Specialist Posts/Services-2023.

-> It will be held on 04.08.2024 (Sunday) in One Sitting through OMR mode.

-> The OSSC CGL Exam 2024 is being conducted for 543 vacancies of various Group B and Group C posts under the Government of Odisha.

-> The selection process includes Prelims, Mains, Skill Test, and Document Verification.

-> To score well in the exam, you may enhance your preparation by solving the OSSC CGL Previous Years' Papers.
